[1
Date: Wed 23 May 2001 13:15:29 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Times of India, Wed 23 May 2001 [edited
<http://www.timesofindia.com/today/23hlth8.htm>

Increase in fatal cases of dengue fever in Thailand
-------------------------------------------
BANGKOK: Heavy rain and warmer weather, coupled with an influx of illegal
aliens, have contributed to an upsurge this year in cases of the
potentially fatal disease dengue fever, health officials said on Tue 22 May
2001. A Public Health Ministry report noted 20 400 cases of dengue fever
nationwide for the first 4 months of this year, a 25 per cent increase over
the 16 267 cases reported for the same period in 2000. Fatal cases of
dengue fever over the same period have increased more than 27 per cent, to
33 from 43. Saravudh Suvannadabba, director of the Ministry's Dengue
Control Division. said that rain was the main problem, because it created
pools of still water where mosquitoes can breed.
